HEADWORD: Revirescence
<hw>Rev`i*res"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>revirescens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>revirescere</ets> to grow green
again.]</ety> <def>A growing green or fresh again; renewal of youth or
vigor.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revisable</ent>⟦br⟧
